<div class="block-contributor">
		

		<div class="block-contributor-content">
		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><span class="smallcaps"><strong>Cheryl Strayed</strong></span> recently completed her first novel, <em>Torch</em>, which is set in rural northern Minnesota, where she grew up. Her fiction and memoir have been published in <em>Double Take</em>, <em>Nerve</em>, <em>Hope Magazine</em>, and several anthologies, including <em>Best New American Voices 2002</em> (Harvest), and <em>Best American Essays 2002</em> (Mariner Books). She lives in Sheffield, Massachusetts, with her husband, the filmmaker Brian Lindstrom, who fills her life with love.</p><a href="/contributors/cheryl-strayed" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
	</div>
</div>

